Summary of What Exists
AthenAI is a well-structured 7-module Python prototype for safety command inference in noisy industrial environments. All modules are coherent, properly import from each other, and the inference pipeline is complete. However, it has never been trained. It is a skeleton awaiting data and training.

Core modules: AudioJEPAEncoder (ViT), SensorEncoder (Transformer), CrossAttentionFusion (8-head cross-attention), CommandClassifier (MLP + MC Dropout), CleanAudioSynthesizer (AudioGen), LLMAlert (OpenAI), Pipeline (AthenAISystem).

Critical Issue: The Audio-JEPA Is Not JEPA
Reading src/encoders/audio_jepa.py directly reveals the problem. The class:

Loads google/vit-base-patch16-224 — an image ViT pretrained on ImageNet
Has a target_encoder (EMA copy) that is never called in forward()
Has no masking strategy, no predictor network, no JEPA training objective
Is essentially: mel-spectrogram → Conv2d patch embed → ViT → embeddings
This is a ViT feature extractor, not a JEPA. It will work but lacks the noise robustness that comes from proper JEPA self-supervised training.

